<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="66" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,258,354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,258,283]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="66" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Dorsal fin rays IV, 22–23; Anal fin rays 1, 16; Pectoral fin rays 19–20; Pelvic fin rays I, 5; Lateral Line scales 39–41. Gill rakers 18–21+ 35–39. Vertebrae 28. Pelvic fins long in males reaching on to anal, black pigmentation between membrane of maxilla and premaxilla (
<bibRefCitation author="Talwar, P. K." box="[750,902,330,354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="66" pagination="87 - 91" refId="ref2270" refString="Talwar, P. K. (1973) A New Bathypelagic Fish, Sphenanthias whiteheadi (Pisces: Owstoniidae), from India. Proceedings of the Zoological Society Calcutta, 25, 87 - 91." type="journal article" year="1973">Talwar, 1973</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
