<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="2" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1745,2024]" pageId="2" pageNumber="66">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,1745,1770]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="66" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Measurements are given in 
<tableCitation box="[664,750,1745,1769]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,235,583,606]" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphometric measurements of Sphenanthias whiteheadi from southwest and southeast coast of India (in % SL)" pageId="2" pageNumber="66">Table.1</tableCitation>
. Values of 
<typeStatus box="[876,924,1746,1770]" pageId="2" pageNumber="66">type</typeStatus>
specimens in 
<bibRefCitation author="Talwar, P. K." box="[1087,1235,1745,1769]" pageId="2" pageNumber="66" pagination="87 - 91" refId="ref2270" refString="Talwar, P. K. (1973) A New Bathypelagic Fish, Sphenanthias whiteheadi (Pisces: Owstoniidae), from India. Proceedings of the Zoological Society Calcutta, 25, 87 - 91." type="journal article" year="1973">Talwar, 1973</bibRefCitation>
follows in parenthesis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1745,2024]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,535]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="67" pageId="2" pageNumber="66">
Body compressed, elongated with tapering tails. Males larger than females. Head large, head length 26.1–31.8 % SL (25.7–30 % SL) 
<quantity box="[405,518,1854,1878]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.763" metricValueMax="9.652" metricValueMin="7.874" pageId="2" pageNumber="66" unit="in" value="3.45" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="3.1">3.1–3.8 in</quantity>
SL (
<quantity box="[572,686,1854,1878]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.143999999999998" metricValueMax="9.906" metricValueMin="8.382" pageId="2" pageNumber="66" unit="in" value="3.5999999999999996" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.9 in</quantity>
SL), body depth at dorsal origin 22.8–28.5% SL (25.1–30.9% SL), eyes large, eye length (bony orbit) 6.1–11.6 % SL (8–9.4% SL), interorbital 5.5–6.8% SL (6–6.9 % SL), mouth large, lower jaw projecting, maxilla broad. Lower margin of preopercle serrated with 6–9 spines. Opercle with small scales. Lateral line runs close to dorsal fin base and ends at dorsal fin last rays mostly at 22 
<superScript attach="left" box="[1254,1269,1961,1975]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="66">nd</superScript>
and 23 
<superScript attach="right" box="[1362,1375,1961,1975]" fontSize="6" pageId="2" pageNumber="66">rd</superScript>
rays. LL scales (pored) 36–38. Teeth in upper jaw uniserial, teeth absent in symphysis of both jaws. Pelvic fins in males elongate (
<figureCitation box="[262,322,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1084,1107]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,407,1062]" captionTargetId="figure-214@2.[151,1436,407,1062]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male, Sphenanthias whiteheadi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5245283" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5245283/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">Fig.2</figureCitation>
) 43–48% SL (43.3–55.6% SL) females (
<figureCitation box="[786,846,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1678,1701]" captionTargetBox="[195,1405,1191,1623]" captionTargetId="figure-218@2.[151,1436,1156,1657]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 3. Female, Sphenanthias whiteheadi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5245287" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5245287/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">Fig.3</figureCitation>
) 24.7–30 % SL (28.8–35.7 % SL). Pelvic fin proximal ray attached to body. Dorsal fin base 64–68.5% SL. The first two dorsal fin spines placed closer than other spines. Caudal fin elongate and lanceolate. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talwar" authorityYear="1973" box="[638,919,224,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cepolidae" genus="Sphenanthias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="whiteheadi">
<emphasis box="[638,919,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">Sphenanthias whiteheadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cannot be mistaken with 
<taxonomicName authority="Smith 1968" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1968" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cepolidae" genus="Sphenanthias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simoterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">Sphenanthias simoterus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, J. L. B." box="[206,339,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref2227" refString="Smith, J. L. B. (1968) New and interesting fishes from deepish water off Durban, Natal and southern Mozambique. South African Association for Marine Biological Research, Investigation Report, 19, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1968">Smith 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1968" box="[350,487,260,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cepolidae" genus="Sphenanthias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simoterus">
<emphasis box="[350,487,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">S. simoterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having peculiar characters; D III, 21; A I, 14; GR 13+ 24, LL 46–48 (
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, J. L. B." box="[1273,1415,260,284]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" pagination="1 - 30" refId="ref2227" refString="Smith, J. L. B. (1968) New and interesting fishes from deepish water off Durban, Natal and southern Mozambique. South African Association for Marine Biological Research, Investigation Report, 19, 1 - 30." type="journal article" year="1968">Smith, 1968</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,535]" box="[197,1340,295,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,367,295,320]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">DNA analysis.</emphasis>
A 652 bp of mitochondrial COI region was amplified bidirectionaly for 
<specimenCount box="[1179,1336,295,319]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,535]" box="[197,862,331,356]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,330,331,356]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Utilization.</emphasis>
The species is primarily used for consumption.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,535]" box="[197,568,367,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,387,367,392]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Common name.</emphasis>
Indian bandfish
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,535]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,404,428]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talwar" authorityYear="1973" box="[528,810,404,428]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cepolidae" genus="Sphenanthias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="whiteheadi">
<emphasis box="[528,810,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">Sphenanthias whiteheadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected off the coast of Tuticorin in the Gulf of Mannar at a depth of 
<quantity box="[400,520,439,463]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" unit="m" value="285.0" valueMax="350.0" valueMin="220.0">220–350m</quantity>
by deep-sea shrimp trawler. The 
<typeStatus box="[905,1003,439,463]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount box="[1061,1233,439,464]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" type="generic" typeStatus="paratypes">three paratypes</specimenCount>
were collected at Quilon, north of Tuticorin, along the southeast coast of 
<collectingCountry box="[771,832,476,500]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">India</collectingCountry>
. This species may prove to be more widespread along the Indian coast.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1436,583,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" startId="3.[151,235,583,606]">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,583,636]" box="[151,1436,583,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,583,606]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">TABLE 1.</emphasis>
Morphometric measurements of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Talwar" authorityYear="1973" box="[606,862,584,606]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cepolidae" genus="Sphenanthias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="67" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="whiteheadi">
<emphasis box="[606,862,584,606]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">Sphenanthias whiteheadi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from southwest and southeast coast of India (in % SL)
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,583,636]" box="[151,207,614,636]" pageId="3" pageNumber="67">(n=8)</paragraph>
